1694
00:55:31,648 --> 00:55:34,277
I had to make my mark through acting.

1695
00:55:34,278 --> 00:55:35,847
I gave it a lot of thought.

1696
00:55:35,848 --> 00:55:39,317
At that time, method acting was all the rage.

1697
00:55:39,318 --> 00:55:41,218
Stanislavski's method acting.

1698
00:55:41,248 --> 00:55:42,987
- So, I went to a church...
- Church?

1699
00:55:42,988 --> 00:55:44,118
and did this.

1700
00:55:44,358 --> 00:55:45,728
- You begged?
- I did.

1701
00:55:46,258 --> 00:55:48,758
- I had a bowl in front of me.
- Okay.

1702
00:55:49,198 --> 00:55:50,357
I begged for money like this.

1703
00:55:50,358 --> 00:55:52,367
- I got quite a lot of money.
- You did?

1704
00:55:52,368 --> 00:55:53,597
How much did you make?

1705
00:55:53,598 --> 00:55:55,167
I don't remember the exact amount,

1706
00:55:55,168 --> 00:55:58,567
but there were dimes and one-dollar bills piled up.

1707
00:55:58,568 --> 00:56:00,567
- Sang Min did that before.
- We don't know...

1708
00:56:00,568 --> 00:56:03,778
much about Ji Won,

1709
00:56:04,078 --> 00:56:06,577
- but for some reason, I think...
- I bet she did it.

1710
00:56:06,578 --> 00:56:09,577
- it would be possible for Ji Won.
- Right.

1711
00:56:09,578 --> 00:56:11,247
It's all about experience.

1712
00:56:11,248 --> 00:56:13,688
- She's even climbed the desert.
- That does sound plausible,

1713
00:56:14,148 --> 00:56:16,787
but your tone of voice has changed compared to earlier.

1714
00:56:16,788 --> 00:56:19,228
- You think so?
- Her voice is shaking.

1715
00:56:19,358 --> 00:56:21,027
- About method acting...
- If it were true,

1716
00:56:21,028 --> 00:56:23,357
- she would be more excited.
- Right. I think so.

1717
00:56:23,358 --> 00:56:24,997
- She sounds calm now.
- Her voice is somewhat low.

1718
00:56:24,998 --> 00:56:26,797
She lowered her head.

1719
00:56:26,798 --> 00:56:28,497
That's not method acting.

1720
00:56:28,498 --> 00:56:30,437
- Exactly.
- You should make eye contact,

1721
00:56:30,438 --> 00:56:32,638
showing people your pitiful side.

1722
00:56:32,808 --> 00:56:34,667
Anyone can bow their head and beg like this.

1723
00:56:34,668 --> 00:56:35,877
It's not about experience.

1724
00:56:35,878 --> 00:56:38,377
She made that up, so she was just acting.

1725
00:56:38,378 --> 00:56:39,847
- That's not true.
- I can tell.

1726
00:56:39,848 --> 00:56:42,177
There are some stories that sound like lies.

1727
00:56:42,178 --> 00:56:44,178
I had a similar experience after my debut.

1728
00:56:44,378 --> 00:56:47,418
I went to a nice place to volunteer one day.

1729
00:56:47,588 --> 00:56:50,518
Back then, I had a bowl-shaped haircut.

1730
00:56:50,558 --> 00:56:52,828
It was when I was doing "Kkeumjjigi."

1731
00:56:53,188 --> 00:56:55,658
I was feeding some little kids.

1732
00:56:55,728 --> 00:56:58,667
While I was doing it, another volunteer fed me.

1733
00:56:58,668 --> 00:56:59,928
- Come on.
- I'm serious.

1734
00:57:00,128 --> 00:57:01,267
- You're...
- It's true.

1735
00:57:01,268 --> 00:57:03,338
- It can happen.
- I'm serious.

1736
00:57:03,598 --> 00:57:05,867
- I'm telling you the truth.
- Come on.

1737
00:57:05,868 --> 00:57:07,067
- No way.
- Hey, friend.

1738
00:57:07,068 --> 00:57:09,538
- Why would I lie about that?
- That's absurd.

1739
00:57:09,638 --> 00:57:11,407
- And...
- I think this is a lie.

1740
00:57:11,408 --> 00:57:12,948
And the fart thing is a lie.

1741
00:57:13,578 --> 00:57:15,777
- Seriously...
- Both are lies.

1742
00:57:15,778 --> 00:57:17,317
- Both of them...
- It can't be true.

1743
00:57:17,318 --> 00:57:19,648
It's not a lie!

1744
00:57:19,748 --> 00:57:21,987
- It's true. It was like this.
- So, did you eat it or not?

1745
00:57:21,988 --> 00:57:23,317
- They went, "I'm so sorry."
- Shin Young, do you...

1746
00:57:23,318 --> 00:57:24,487
- keep making things up like that..
- I'm serious.

1747
00:57:24,488 --> 00:57:25,658
in your head?

1748
00:57:25,758 --> 00:57:29,028
I didn't make them up. It's true!

1749
00:57:29,658 --> 00:57:31,667
I'm Lucia. I even have...

1750
00:57:31,668 --> 00:57:33,427
a baptismal name. I'm Lucia.

1751
00:57:33,428 --> 00:57:36,397
I'll tell the nun at Cheongsu Cathedral about this.

1752
00:57:36,398 --> 00:57:37,967
I guess it could really happen.

1753
00:57:37,968 --> 00:57:40,068
- I'm serious.
- Then, Ji Won, what's number three?

1754
00:57:40,238 --> 00:57:41,538
- In which country?
- That's really...

1755
00:57:41,568 --> 00:57:42,707
- It happened in Korea.
- Korea?

1756
00:57:42,708 --> 00:57:44,707
- In Korea?
- It happened in Korea?

1757
00:57:44,708 --> 00:57:46,107
- Seoul?
- Yes, in Seoul, Korea.

1758
00:57:46,108 --> 00:57:47,747
Then, you must've been drunk.

1759
00:57:47,748 --> 00:57:49,777
- No, I didn't drink.
- You were sober?

1760
00:57:49,778 --> 00:57:50,877
She rarely drinks.

1761
00:57:50,878 --> 00:57:52,517
Why did you dance there?

1762
00:57:52,518 --> 00:57:54,848
- Tell us exactly what happened.
- Give us the full situation.

1763
00:57:55,088 --> 00:57:57,788
When I was on the drama, "Should We Kiss First?,"

1764
00:57:58,018 --> 00:57:59,627
the production crew gave me homework.

1765
00:57:59,628 --> 00:58:01,157
- Listen. Her voice changes...
- So...

1766
00:58:01,158 --> 00:58:02,828
when she tells a lie.

1767
00:58:03,528 --> 00:58:05,027
You're right. Her voice changes.

1768
00:58:05,028 --> 00:58:06,967
- She is so bad at telling a lie.
- She got caught.

1769
00:58:06,968 --> 00:58:08,297
It's a lie!

1770
00:58:08,298 --> 00:58:09,598
- Anyway, that happened.
- Okay.

1771
00:58:10,038 --> 00:58:12,037
- I have that scene in a drama.
- She is acting again.

1772
00:58:12,038 --> 00:58:13,038
Right away.

1773
00:58:13,438 --> 00:58:15,177
People watched that scene,

1774
00:58:15,178 --> 00:58:18,208
and I got another homework for the drama, "Brain Works."

1775
00:58:18,308 --> 00:58:20,047
- What homework?
- They watched that scene...

1776
00:58:20,048 --> 00:58:21,377
and asked me to pole dance again.

1777
00:58:21,378 --> 00:58:24,548
But doing it inside in the same way wouldn't have been fun.

1778
00:58:25,018 --> 00:58:27,087
You know how there is a road sign on the street?

1779
00:58:27,088 --> 00:58:29,157
They asked me to pole dance there, and I agreed.

1780
00:58:29,158 --> 00:58:31,418
When I was learning...

1781
00:58:31,728 --> 00:58:33,987
how to pole dance, they told me...

1782
00:58:33,988 --> 00:58:36,028
that I'd want to hang on to a road sign...

1783
00:58:36,358 --> 00:58:38,667
or a random pole on the street...

1784
00:58:38,668 --> 00:58:40,868
once I became accustomed to pole dancing.

1785
00:58:41,528 --> 00:58:42,567
They told me that I'd do it sober.

1786
00:58:42,568 --> 00:58:44,367
They told me that I'd do it more before a crowd...

1787
00:58:44,368 --> 00:58:45,737
- That's right.
- in order to show off.

1788
00:58:45,738 --> 00:58:47,007
When I was learning how to rock climb,

1789
00:58:47,008 --> 00:58:48,777
I wanted to climb the walls.

1790
00:58:48,778 --> 00:58:49,937
- What?
- Right.

1791
00:58:49,938 --> 00:58:51,637
- It's a lie.
- I'm serious.

1792
00:58:51,638 --> 00:58:53,147
When you learn how to play pool,

1793
00:58:53,148 --> 00:58:54,807
you see billiard balls on the ceiling.

1794
00:58:54,808 --> 00:58:56,347
- That happens.
- That's right.

1795
00:58:56,348 --> 00:58:58,317
- You imagine them.
- You see them.

1796
00:58:58,318 --> 00:59:00,587
- Ji Won has a point.
- Right?

1797
00:59:00,588 --> 00:59:02,317
Once I became pretty good at it,

1798
00:59:02,318 --> 00:59:04,587
I wanted to show off to my friends.

1799
00:59:04,588 --> 00:59:07,327
- Right.
- I did it in two dramas, after all.

1800
00:59:07,328 --> 00:59:08,758
So I was on the street...

1801
00:59:09,098 --> 00:59:10,758
when I gave a demonstration.

1802
00:59:11,258 --> 00:59:13,368
I gave a demonstration a few times.

1803
00:59:13,968 --> 00:59:17,138
On one occasion, it got bent.

1804
00:59:17,798 --> 00:59:18,937
- The road sign?
- The pole?

1805
00:59:18,938 --> 00:59:20,767
- It got bent a bit.
- The pole got bent.

1806
00:59:20,768 --> 00:59:22,777
My friends erupted in laughter.

1807
00:59:22,778 --> 00:59:25,077
They erupted in laughter.

1808
00:59:25,078 --> 00:59:27,877
We were in an area that was sensitive to the noise.

1809
00:59:27,878 --> 00:59:29,347
- We were supposed to be quiet.
- You destroyed public property.

1810
00:59:29,348 --> 00:59:30,777
People thought we were drunk.

1811
00:59:30,778 --> 00:59:32,587
- Right.
- We weren't drunk,

1812
00:59:32,588 --> 00:59:34,088
but they misunderstood and called the police.

1813
00:59:34,318 --> 00:59:36,687
- When did it happen?
- It happened years ago.

1814
00:59:36,688 --> 00:59:38,487
About five years ago.

1815
00:59:38,488 --> 00:59:40,827
- I think it actually happened.
- But you were already famous then.

1816
00:59:40,828 --> 00:59:41,828
- Yes.
- That's right.

1817
00:59:41,829 --> 00:59:43,657
I don't think it makes sense.

1818
00:59:43,658 --> 00:59:44,658
- That's right.
- Let's say...

1819
00:59:44,858 --> 00:59:47,427
she went to the police station...

1820
00:59:47,428 --> 00:59:49,297
for pole dancing on a street sign.

1821
00:59:49,298 --> 00:59:50,737
- There would've been articles.
- Articles.

1822
00:59:50,738 --> 00:59:52,067
- It would've made the news.
- That's right.

1823
00:59:52,068 --> 00:59:53,637
- It didn't make the news.
- No way.

1824
00:59:53,638 --> 00:59:56,207
- It didn't make the news.
- It would've made the news.

1825
00:59:56,208 --> 00:59:57,938
They didn't recognize me.

1826
00:59:58,748 --> 01:00:00,277
- I'm serious.
- Ji Won,

1827
01:00:00,278 --> 01:00:01,877
I'd understand...

1828
01:00:01,878 --> 01:00:04,247
if a passing police officer saw you...

1829
01:00:04,248 --> 01:00:06,488
- and made you pay a fine...
- That's right.

1830
01:00:06,688 --> 01:00:08,757
- even if you were a celebrity.
- That's right.

1831
01:00:08,758 --> 01:00:10,517
- But the police station?
- Did you go to the substation?

1832
01:00:10,518 --> 01:00:11,587
- You went to the police substation.
- I did.

1833
01:00:11,588 --> 01:00:12,757
- Did you go to the police station?
- Did you?

1834
01:00:12,758 --> 01:00:14,127
- I went there.
- What did you do?

1835
01:00:14,128 --> 01:00:16,257
I told them...

1836
01:00:16,258 --> 01:00:17,957
because I couldn't get out of the situation.

1837
01:00:17,958 --> 01:00:20,827
- "I'm Yeh Ji Won."
- "I'm Yeh Ji Won."

1838
01:00:20,828 --> 01:00:22,897
They told me not to lie.

1839
01:00:22,898 --> 01:00:26,408
Did the police go, "Sure. I'm Jung Bo Seog?"

1840
01:00:26,508 --> 01:00:27,508
(She was mistaken for a Yeh Ji Won lookalike.)

1841
01:00:27,509 --> 01:00:29,007
- They thought it was a lie.
- Then...

1842
01:00:29,008 --> 01:00:31,237
- It wasn't even a substation.
- How did you get released?

1843
01:00:31,238 --> 01:00:33,447
When you told them that you were Yeh Ji Won, they didn't believe you.

1844
01:00:33,448 --> 01:00:34,848
I called my manager.

1845
01:00:35,318 --> 01:00:37,547
- Even if there was a report, - They believed me when he came.

1846
01:00:37,548 --> 01:00:39,687
- she wouldn't have gotten arrested.
- A manager from the agency.

1847
01:00:39,688 --> 01:00:41,687
I've taught Ji Won...

1848
01:00:41,688 --> 01:00:43,087
- Right.
- on "High School Girls."

1849
01:00:43,088 --> 01:00:44,318
I know what Ji Won is like.

1850
01:00:44,618 --> 01:00:45,757
It's number two.

1851
01:00:45,758 --> 01:00:48,657
When it's something she has done, she talks excitedly.

1852
01:00:48,658 --> 01:00:50,457
But since this is something she hasn't done,

1853
01:00:50,458 --> 01:00:51,897
- her tone becomes uncertain.
- You know,

1854
01:00:51,898 --> 01:00:53,227
- I wish...
- I think it's number three.

1855
01:00:53,228 --> 01:00:55,398
- Bo Seog gets it wrong.
- Seriously.

1856
01:00:55,668 --> 01:00:57,767
- He is so certain. Right?
- I...

1857
01:00:57,768 --> 01:00:59,507
I want Jo Pil Yeon to get it wrong.

1858
01:00:59,508 --> 01:01:00,767
Let's see if Bo Seog is right.

1859
01:01:00,768 --> 01:01:02,077
- Let's go.
- Let's do this.

1860
01:01:02,078 --> 01:01:03,608
- It's confusing, right?
- Now,

1861
01:01:03,938 --> 01:01:06,507
if you think the statement about her flying off the stage...

1862
01:01:06,508 --> 01:01:08,517
- during a play is a lie, - It could happen.

1863
01:01:08,518 --> 01:01:09,518
raise your hand.

1864
01:01:09,748 --> 01:01:10,877
(Hee Chul chooses number 1.)

1865
01:01:10,878 --> 01:01:12,787
- Hee Chul.
- I think it's a cunning lie...

1866
01:01:12,788 --> 01:01:14,818
she has come up with in order to promote the play,

1867
01:01:15,018 --> 01:01:16,717
- "Hongdo: A Tragic Love Story."
- It's fake.

1868
01:01:16,718 --> 01:01:18,657
- Really?
- You have a point.

1869
01:01:18,658 --> 01:01:20,357
- You could be right.
- The play in the statement is...

1870
01:01:20,358 --> 01:01:21,587
- "Hongdo: A Tragic Love Story."
- Is that it?

1871
01:01:21,588 --> 01:01:24,098
- You're sharp.
- I had the same thought.

1872
01:01:24,728 --> 01:01:26,727
But I reasoned that she brought a true story...

1873
01:01:26,728 --> 01:01:28,867
- in order to promote the play.
- That's right.

1874
01:01:28,868 --> 01:01:30,337
- A true story.
- That's my deduction.

1875
01:01:30,338 --> 01:01:31,397
- Okay.
- You're sharp.

1876
01:01:31,398 --> 01:01:32,567
The play in which she flew off the stage is...

1877
01:01:32,568 --> 01:01:33,737
- "Hongdo: A Tragic Love Story."
- People want to see her spin.

1878
01:01:33,738 --> 01:01:35,507
- That's right.
- Yes. So it has to be true.

1879
01:01:35,508 --> 01:01:37,407
- Hee Chul's reasoning made me go, - It made me unsure.

1880
01:01:37,408 --> 01:01:38,747
- "Hold on."
- Right?

1881
01:01:38,748 --> 01:01:40,478
"The Yeh Ji Won I know..."

1882
01:01:40,948 --> 01:01:43,077
- "could do that."
- You were so certain before.

1883
01:01:43,078 --> 01:01:45,687
You were so certain that number one was true.

1884
01:01:45,688 --> 01:01:47,917
- Are you sure you know her?
- Isn't this the character...

1885
01:01:47,918 --> 01:01:49,657
- of Jewelry Jung?
- Jo Pil Yeon.

1886
01:01:49,658 --> 01:01:51,257
- Yes. "High Kick Through The Roof."
- Listen.

1887
01:01:51,258 --> 01:01:52,727
- In "High Kick Through The Roof..."
- He is swayed so easily.

1888
01:01:52,728 --> 01:01:56,227
Ji Won is serious about promoting "Hongdo: A Tragic Love Story."

1889
01:01:56,228 --> 01:01:57,228
- That's right.
- Of course.

1890
01:01:57,229 --> 01:01:59,067
- She does it so diligently.
- She always wants to do more.

1891
01:01:59,068 --> 01:02:00,227
- Yes.
- So...

1892
01:02:00,228 --> 01:02:01,297
You said the answer was number two.

1893
01:02:01,298 --> 01:02:02,797
Let's raise our hands again.

1894
01:02:02,798 --> 01:02:04,267
- You were the one who persuaded us.
- Let's raise our hands again.

1895
01:02:04,268 --> 01:02:05,907
- Number two.
- Let's do it again.

1896
01:02:05,908 --> 01:02:06,967
- Number 2.
- Number 2.

1897
01:02:06,968 --> 01:02:09,738
"I have begged for acting."

1898
01:02:10,138 --> 01:02:11,947
- In 1, 2, 3.
- She wouldn't have begged.

1899
01:02:11,948 --> 01:02:13,377
- For a play...
- I'm sure she did something else...

1900
01:02:13,378 --> 01:02:14,877
- for acting.
- Ji Won.

1901
01:02:14,878 --> 01:02:16,077
She would've danced...

1902
01:02:16,078 --> 01:02:17,577
or done something else.

1903
01:02:17,578 --> 01:02:20,117
- She wouldn't have begged.
- Now, number three.

1904
01:02:20,118 --> 01:02:23,157
"I once went to the police station for pole dancing..."

1905
01:02:23,158 --> 01:02:24,957
"while hanging from a street sign."

1906
01:02:24,958 --> 01:02:26,827
- There is no way...
- But it suits her character.

1907
01:02:26,828 --> 01:02:28,527
people would report her to the police...

1908
01:02:28,528 --> 01:02:30,397
- for something so trivial.
- The police station is too much.

1909
01:02:30,398 --> 01:02:32,468
- It would've made the news.
- People make many reports.

1910
01:02:32,798 --> 01:02:35,437
- Should I reveal it now?
- Which one is the lie?

1911
01:02:35,438 --> 01:02:36,937
(Which one is Ji Won's lie?)

1912
01:02:36,938 --> 01:02:38,268
- Which one is it?
- Which one is it?

1913
01:02:38,838 --> 01:02:40,037
- Which one is it?
- Which one is it?

1914
01:02:40,038 --> 01:02:41,038
Which number?

1915
01:02:41,168 --> 01:02:42,177
- Which number?
- My guess is begging.

1916
01:02:42,178 --> 01:02:43,178
All right.

1917
01:02:43,308 --> 01:02:44,377
(Had she gone to the police station, it would've made headlines.)

1918
01:02:44,378 --> 01:02:45,378
What's the answer?

1919
01:02:45,778 --> 01:02:47,448
- What's the answer?
- It's number three.

1920
01:02:47,648 --> 01:02:49,717
See? She stuttered the most while explaining number three.

1921
01:02:49,718 --> 01:02:51,217
- Really?
- Her story got messed up.

1922
01:02:51,218 --> 01:02:52,487
- No way.
- Really?

1923
01:02:52,488 --> 01:02:54,587
- Bo Seog doesn't know anything.
- What was that?

1924
01:02:54,588 --> 01:02:55,687
What was that?

1925
01:02:55,688 --> 01:02:57,817
- Bo Seog doesn't know anything.
- Come on.

1926
01:02:57,818 --> 01:02:59,127
I got it wrong because of him.

1927
01:02:59,128 --> 01:03:00,827
- He wasn't perfect.
- Come on.

1928
01:03:00,828 --> 01:03:02,558
- I mean...
- Ji Won.

1929
01:03:02,858 --> 01:03:05,267
- You are good at lying.
